---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { LanguageBoot } from "../components/LanguageBoot";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Tonet Handbook"
  description="Tonet handbook: complete public documentation for users, operators, and contributors."
  page="handbook"
>
  <main class="section pt-10">
    <h1 class="mb-2 text-4xl">Public handbook</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      This page centralizes expanded project documentation: use cases, utility references, product evolution, and future implementation tracks.
    </p>

    <article class="mb-4 card">
      <h2 class="mt-0">Use cases</h2>
      <ul class="leading-relaxed text-[#9aa3b5]">
        <li>Low-overhead browsing in controlled environments.</li>
        <li>Educational and R&amp;D contexts where browser internals must stay transparent.</li>
        <li>Operational deployment where CDN-based release distribution is required.</li>
        <li>Security-conscious setups that prefer explicit policy-driven behavior.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="mb-4 card">
      <h2 class="mt-0">Utilities and internal pages</h2>
      <ul class="leading-relaxed text-[#9aa3b5]">
        <li><code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">tonet://settings</code>: language, theme, update policy, system toggles.</li>
        <li><code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">tonet://downloads</code>: page fetch and local save activity.</li>
        <li><code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">tonet://history</code>: visit timeline and data management hooks.</li>
        <li><code class="rounded bg-white/[0.06] px-1">tonet://new-tab</code>: shortcuts and search integration.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="mb-4 card">
      <h2 class="mt-0">Recent changes</h2>
      <p class="text-[#9aa3b5]">
        Recent work focuses on Servo integration foundations, improved policy surfaces, update flow hardening, and stronger CI/document
        reproducibility. Full version notes are tracked in the changelog section after each release.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="mb-4 card">
      <h2 class="mt-0">Future implementation tracks</h2>
      <ul class="leading-relaxed text-[#9aa3b5]">
        <li>Broader selector/layout support for improved compatibility.</li>
        <li>Expanded cross-platform packaging and installer parity.</li>
        <li>More complete test matrices for conformance and regressions.</li>
        <li>Incremental performance and memory budget enforcement.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2 class="mt-0">Comparison notes</h2>
      <p class="text-[#9aa3b5]">
        Tonet is intentionally narrower than mature browsers like Chrome and Brave. It targets clarity, policy control, and operational determinism first. See <a
          class="text-[#4f8cff] hover:underline"
          href="/compare.html">Compare</a> for a concise positioning summary.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>

  <p class="mx-auto max-w-[1120px] px-6 pb-10 text-center text-[#9aa3b5]">
    <a class="text-[#4f8cff] hover:underline" href="/docs.html">Back to docs portal</a>
  </p>
  <LanguageBoot client:load />
</BaseLayout>
